1
00:02:09,519 --> 00:02:13,017
{\an1}<i>For the next three days, I'm</i>
<i>gonna give it everything I've</i>
<i>got...</i>

2
00:02:14,349 --> 00:02:15,682
{\an1}<i>...for Lord Gaara</i>

3
00:02:28,841 --> 00:02:31,840
{\an1}<i>Lord Gaara, putting up your Sand</i>
<i>Guard won't help you train.  </i>

4
00:02:33,339 --> 00:02:33,806
Sorry.

5
00:02:35,038 --> 00:02:38,170
{\an1}My Sand Guard's a automatic
response, not a conscious one.

6
00:02:38,569 --> 00:02:40,169
{\an1}Your Sand is like armor.

7
00:02:41,002 --> 00:02:44,167
{\an1}<i>Even if it's solid, you'll still</i>
<i>sustain damage... </i>

8
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:46,232
{\an1}...if your taijutsu's weak.

9
00:02:46,565 --> 00:02:48,596
{\an1}[thud, heavy breathing]

10
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:51,196
{\an1}Just stay on the offensive and
maintain your breathing.

11
00:02:52,661 --> 00:02:54,660
{\an1}<i>Then your body will move</i>
<i>naturally. </i>

12
00:02:55,727 --> 00:02:56,427
[pow]

13
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:56,826
<i>So now... </i>

14
00:02:57,592 --> 00:02:58,292
{\an1}<i>...try to defend yourself...</i>

15
00:02:59,392 --> 00:03:00,657
{\an1}<i>... before your Sand Guard</i>
<i>activates. </i>

16
00:03:01,457 --> 00:03:07,154
[thwack]

17
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,053
[growl]

18
00:03:09,086 --> 00:03:13,784
[clunk]

19
00:03:13,817 --> 00:03:15,216
[thump, swish]

20
00:03:16,882 --> 00:03:18,114
{\an1}I'm impressed, Lord Gaara.

21
00:03:19,148 --> 00:03:21,479
{\an1}<i>You've progressed so much in</i>
<i>such a short time. </i>

22
00:03:22,312 --> 00:03:27,476
{\an4}<i>Once you master taijutsu, you'll</i>
<i>be able to combine it with your</i>
<i>Sand Guard to make it even more</i>
<i>formidable. </i>

23
00:03:28,143 --> 00:03:29,475
{\an1}<i>It's all thanks to you.</i>

24
00:03:30,974 --> 00:03:33,973
{\an1}<i>Shira, are you taking the Chunin</i>
<i>Exams? </i>

25
00:03:34,006 --> 00:03:34,772
Yes.

26
00:03:36,271 --> 00:03:40,535
{\an1}I'm eternally grateful for the
opportunity. Thank you for
giving it to me.

27
00:03:42,301 --> 00:03:44,267
{\an1}Of course. You have the skills.

28
00:03:45,732 --> 00:03:50,231
{\an1}<i>I know in time, you'll become a</i>
<i>great shinobi of the Sand. </i>

29
00:03:52,895 --> 00:03:55,727
{\an1}<i>They're finally here!</i>
<i>The Chunin Exams!</i>

30
00:03:56,227 --> 00:03:57,892
{\an1}<i>I'm getting kinda antsy.</i>

31
00:03:59,059 --> 00:04:00,891
{\an1}<i>It's too soon to get nervous.</i>

32
00:04:02,290 --> 00:04:05,355
{\an1}Our goal isn't simply to pass
the Chunin Exams ourselves,...

33
00:04:06,222 --> 00:04:09,552
{\an1}<i>...but to have as many Sand</i>
<i>entrants as possible pass. </i>

34
00:04:11,019 --> 00:04:13,517
{\an1}That will be my way of repaying
Lord Gaara.

35
00:04:14,516 --> 00:04:17,582
{\an1}Wow, Shira! When your mind's
made up, you don't budge!

36
00:04:19,148 --> 00:04:22,545
{\an1}I want...to live up to his
expectations.

37
00:04:24,544 --> 00:04:29,275
{\an1}<i>By the way,...this time around,</i>
<i>the Chunin Exams are shorter</i>
<i>than they were before. </i>

38
00:04:29,309 --> 00:04:33,040
{\an1}<i>Yes, it is three days this time</i>
<i>as opposed to five days. </i>

39
00:04:34,007 --> 00:04:38,237
{\an1}Simply put, what that really
means is this place is just that
much more dangerous.

40
00:04:39,371 --> 00:04:44,533
{\an4}<i>When the sun rises, the</i>
<i>temperatures soar in the desert.</i>
<i>And getting around will become</i>
<i>very difficult. </i>

41
00:04:45,034 --> 00:04:45,699
<i>I see...</i>

42
00:04:47,366 --> 00:04:50,365
{\an1}So what you're saying is we may
barely have enough time to
make it to the goal.

43
00:04:50,730 --> 00:04:52,529
{\an1}Then we cannot stop for
anything!

44
00:04:53,062 --> 00:04:56,827
{\an1}Either way, our priority is to
acquire the scroll quickly.

45
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,891
{\an1}To do that we'll have to battle
another team.

46
00:05:00,225 --> 00:05:03,024
{\an1}<i>But still, we can't just pick</i>
<i>any team.</i>

47
00:05:03,522 --> 00:05:05,023
{\an1}<i>I came up with something.</i>

48
00:05:05,456 --> 00:05:06,322
{\an1}What is it, Neji?

49
00:05:08,021 --> 00:05:11,186
{\an1}<i>Yesterday's brawl in the</i>
<i>cafeteria was a fortunate turn</i>
<i>of events. </i>

50
00:05:12,019 --> 00:05:15,883
{\an1}<i>I was able to get a rough idea</i>
<i>of the other teams' strengths. </i>

51
00:05:16,882 --> 00:05:19,648
[wham, thud]

52
00:05:19,681 --> 00:05:25,012
{\an1}<i>In my opinion, the teams to</i>
<i>watch are the one with Shira,</i>
<i>who stopped Lee's kick.  </i>

53
00:05:26,445 --> 00:05:26,944
And then...

54
00:05:31,008 --> 00:05:35,906
[clank, boom]

55
00:05:36,339 --> 00:05:41,669
{\an4}<i>The team from the Hidden</i>
<i>Waterfall. With our skills, we</i>
<i>should have no problems with the</i>
<i>rest of the teams. </i>

56
00:05:42,402 --> 00:05:45,900
{\an1}You're amazing, Neji! You
analyzed all of that already?!

57
00:05:46,267 --> 00:05:49,664
{\an1}So we'll avoid the strong teams
and aim for the weaker ones,
is that right?

58
00:05:49,998 --> 00:05:50,497
<i>But,...</i>

59
00:05:51,463 --> 00:05:53,595
{\an1}I do not like to do things in
that way...

60
00:05:54,462 --> 00:05:57,094
{\an1}Yes,...I figured you might say
that, Lee.

61
00:05:57,927 --> 00:06:04,190
{\an1}<i>But we've waited two and a half</i>
<i>years for these Chunin Exams.</i>
<i>You don't want to fail, do you? </i>

62
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:05,989
No, but I...

63
00:06:07,256 --> 00:06:08,654
<i>But...I...</i>

64
00:06:08,688 --> 00:06:13,584
{\an1}<i>Determination never betrays you.</i>

65
00:06:14,252 --> 00:06:15,084
<i>I want...</i>

66
00:06:16,582 --> 00:06:18,083
<i>...to fight him!</i>

67
00:06:26,412 --> 00:06:27,278
[kapow]

68
00:06:27,312 --> 00:06:28,576
{\an1}<i>There's the start signal.</i>

69
00:06:29,044 --> 00:06:29,742
<i>Let's go!</i>

70
00:06:43,769 --> 00:06:47,933
[hiss]

71
00:06:51,730 --> 00:06:53,230
{\an1}<i>So, what do we do?</i>

72
00:06:55,195 --> 00:06:58,328
{\an1}We were told not to enter the
Demon Desert, so what now?

73
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,959
{\an1}<i>I have a message from Lady</i>
<i>Tsunade. </i>

74
00:07:08,554 --> 00:07:09,687
<i>[hum]</i>

75
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,553
<i>What is it?</i>

76
00:07:10,887 --> 00:07:12,886
{\an1}<i>Uh, huh...I'll read it...</i>

77
00:07:15,450 --> 00:07:20,714
{\an4}<i>"According to intel from agents</i>
<i>who've just returned, opposition</i>
<i>forces have been on the move</i>
<i>recently in the Land of Wind."</i>

78
00:07:21,547 --> 00:07:22,546
{\an1}<i>In other words...</i>

79
00:07:24,412 --> 00:07:27,379
{\an1}<i>...the anti-Gaara faction. An</i>
<i>assassination attempt has</i>
<i>already occurred. </i>

80
00:07:28,211 --> 00:07:32,942
{\an4}<i>In spite of this, supervisors</i>
<i>from other villages are</i>
<i>prohibited from entering the</i>
<i>Demon Desert,...</i>

81
00:07:32,975 --> 00:07:37,472
{\an1}<i>and Gaara himself intends to</i>
<i>supervise the Second Exam as a</i>
<i>proctor. </i>

82
00:07:38,206 --> 00:07:43,370
{\an1}<i>Needless to say, the danger is</i>
<i>enormous if Gaara plans to set</i>
<i>himself up as a decoy. </i>

83
00:07:44,534 --> 00:07:47,866
{\an1}<i>Not only to Gaara, but to the</i>
<i>Hidden Leaf Village as well.  </i>

84
00:07:49,531 --> 00:07:54,696
{\an1}<i>If anything happens to Gaara...</i>
<i>our alliance with the Hidden</i>
<i>Sand will become unstable. </i>

85
00:07:55,528 --> 00:07:58,195
{\an1}<i>Guy,...Aduma,...Kurenai,...</i>

86
00:07:58,693 --> 00:08:02,193
{\an1}<i>Sneak into the Demon Desert and</i>
<i>investigate the Hidden Sand's</i>
<i>movements.</i>

87
00:08:02,892 --> 00:08:06,389
{\an1}<i>And if Gaara's safety is</i>
<i>threatened, then protect him!" </i>

88
00:08:07,722 --> 00:08:08,955
What? Assassins?

89
00:08:10,387 --> 00:08:12,987
{\an1}Gaara himself is the decoy...?

90
00:08:13,552 --> 00:08:16,751
{\an1}The Hidden Sand Village must be
at their wit's end over this...

91
00:08:16,784 --> 00:08:19,916
{\an1}Whatever happens, we must
protect the Kazekage!

92
00:08:20,815 --> 00:08:21,882
Right. Yes.

93
00:08:22,282 --> 00:08:22,947
<i>Scatter!</i>

94
00:08:39,671 --> 00:08:41,537
{\an1}Your eyesight is amazing, Yome.

95
00:08:41,904 --> 00:08:46,034
{\an1}To see what's reflected on a
water droplet that's dozens of
kilometers away...

96
00:08:46,901 --> 00:08:50,266
{\an1}And once she fixes on the relay
point, she can see even farther!

97
00:08:50,799 --> 00:08:55,030
{\an1}But,...the sun dries the water
so I can't use it, for long.

98
00:08:57,595 --> 00:08:59,827
{\an1}<i>I see them! That's the Hidden</i>
<i>Leaf! </i>

99
00:08:59,861 --> 00:09:03,391
{\an1}<i>The Hidden Sand is close by,</i>
<i>too! </i>

100
00:09:03,425 --> 00:09:05,924
{\an1}<i>Send the Sand a signal to stay</i>
<i>away from the Leaf. </i>

101
00:09:06,290 --> 00:09:07,157
<i>Right.</i>

102
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:12,553
[gasp]

103
00:09:13,287 --> 00:09:14,752
{\an1}<i>It's a signal from Shira.</i>

104
00:09:17,284 --> 00:09:19,816
{\an1}<i>Well? Do you see anybody, Neji?</i>

105
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:20,949
{\an1}<i>No, there's no one.</i>

106
00:09:22,381 --> 00:09:24,580
{\an1}<i>But ther has to be. We've run</i>
<i>really far into the desert!</i>

107
00:09:27,912 --> 00:09:30,077
{\an1}<i>What is going on...?</i>

108
00:09:31,410 --> 00:09:33,741
{\an1}<i>Why can't I find anyone with my</i>
<i>Byakugan?</i>

109
00:09:35,075 --> 00:09:38,073
{\an1}<i>Neji, Tenten! Please! Come here!</i>

110
00:09:40,239 --> 00:09:41,171
<i>What is it, Lee?</i>

111
00:09:44,070 --> 00:09:45,303
[clank]

112
00:09:47,568 --> 00:09:49,899
{\an1}I am positive that this is my
kunai.

113
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:51,399
<i>What?!</i>

114
00:09:53,098 --> 00:09:57,395
{\an1}In case we got lost, I stuck a
few kunai in some rocks when
we were running by them.

115
00:09:57,662 --> 00:09:59,761
{\an1}<i>But finding this here means that</i>
<i>we...</i>

116
00:10:00,261 --> 00:10:00,661
[gasp]

117
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:03,659
{\an1}We've merely been running around
in circles...

118
00:10:04,293 --> 00:10:05,891
<i>Is it genjutsu?</i>

119
00:10:06,091 --> 00:10:09,256
{\an1}No way! We haven't even
confronted an enemy yet!

120
00:10:16,252 --> 00:10:16,718
<i>Release!</i>

121
00:10:24,747 --> 00:10:25,380
I knew it...

122
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,046
<i>What's going on?</i>

123
00:10:27,246 --> 00:10:27,779
[gasp]

124
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:29,711
<i>There!</i>

125
00:10:30,377 --> 00:10:31,377
<i>I found them!</i>

126
00:10:34,475 --> 00:10:38,640
{\an1}<i>Let's hurry! According to Shira,</i>
<i>there are some pesky Leaf</i>
<i>shinobi nearby!</i>

127
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:42,471
{\an1}<i>Why should we bother listening</i>
<i>to that guy, anyway?! </i>

128
00:10:43,303 --> 00:10:45,302
{\an1}<i>He's useful to us for now.</i>

129
00:10:45,969 --> 00:10:48,801
{\an1}We can thank him later...with
our fists!

130
00:10:50,966 --> 00:10:52,532
{\an1}Damn! They found us!

131
00:10:52,565 --> 00:10:55,596
{\an1}Now, we don't need to be nice to
these guys, right?

132
00:10:56,463 --> 00:10:57,829
{\an1}No way! Get the scroll!

133
00:10:58,229 --> 00:10:58,962
All right!

134
00:11:00,795 --> 00:11:02,094
<i>Here I go!</i>

135
00:11:02,127 --> 00:11:03,592
[thud, shouting]

136
00:11:03,959 --> 00:11:04,725
<i>Leaf...</i>

137
00:11:07,957 --> 00:11:08,956
<i>Whirlwind!  </i>

138
00:11:09,289 --> 00:11:11,256
[wham]

139
00:11:11,288 --> 00:11:12,788
<i>Datsuji! Goji!</i>

140
00:11:14,154 --> 00:11:15,254
[gasp]

141
00:11:15,286 --> 00:11:17,186
{\an1}<i>You're already within my </i>
<i>range.</i>

142
00:11:17,219 --> 00:11:21,382
{\an1}<i>And I'm going to deal with you</i>
<i>swiftly.</i>

143
00:11:22,382 --> 00:11:23,182
{\an1}Eight Trigrams...

144
00:11:23,948 --> 00:11:24,680
Two Palms!

145
00:11:24,714 --> 00:11:25,114
[gasp]

146
00:11:26,713 --> 00:11:28,445
What?! 4 Palms!

147
00:11:30,146 --> 00:11:30,878
8 Palms!

148
00:11:32,276 --> 00:11:33,276
16 Palms!

149
00:11:34,442 --> 00:11:35,609
32 Palms!

150
00:11:37,774 --> 00:11:39,439
64 Palms!

151
00:11:42,872 --> 00:11:43,337
[growl]

152
00:11:45,603 --> 00:11:46,935
{\an1}He blocked every one?

153
00:11:48,934 --> 00:11:49,768
<i>Shira!</i>

154
00:11:50,933 --> 00:11:53,766
{\an1}<i>We'll handle the Lead. Leave</i>
<i>while you can.</i>

155
00:11:54,297 --> 00:11:55,098
[grunt]

156
00:11:56,131 --> 00:11:58,262
{\an1}I cannot believe I get to fight
you so soon!

157
00:11:58,996 --> 00:12:01,694
{\an1}What's that?! What are you so
happy about, Lee?!

158
00:12:01,727 --> 00:12:03,659
{\an1}Don't fight him carelessly!

159
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,159
<i>Oh, too bad...</i>

160
00:12:06,025 --> 00:12:08,590
{\an1}The Cactus Genjutsu got broken
already, huh?

161
00:12:08,990 --> 00:12:10,355
<i>Cactus Genjutsu?</i>

162
00:12:11,422 --> 00:12:15,420
[hiss]

163
00:12:15,986 --> 00:12:18,852
{\an1}Back then, I did catch a faint
floral scent...

164
00:12:19,851 --> 00:12:21,151
{\an1}That was the genjutsu?

165
00:12:23,116 --> 00:12:26,581
{\an4}We were aware that the Second
Round was gonna take
place right here within the
Demon Desert.

166
00:12:27,346 --> 00:12:30,213
{\an1}So we set up several jutsu as
traps in advance.

167
00:12:31,178 --> 00:12:35,043
{\an1}But don't hold it against us. We
just happen to have te advantage
here.

168
00:12:35,743 --> 00:12:37,575
{\an1}But you do not have it this
time!

169
00:12:38,074 --> 00:12:39,407
{\an1}<i>I wouldn't be to sure of that...</i>

170
00:12:40,006 --> 00:12:40,973
[gasps]

171
00:12:43,005 --> 00:12:46,236
{\an4}I'm usually very cautious, so if
I'm willing to confront you like
this,what do you think that
means...?

172
00:12:50,001 --> 00:12:50,633
[gasp] <i>What?!</i>

173
00:12:50,667 --> 00:12:51,667
I cannot move!

174
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,166
<i>No, not again!</i>
!

175
00:12:55,165 --> 00:12:57,164
{\an1}Oh, I'll release it for you this
time.

176
00:12:57,996 --> 00:12:58,796
Release!

177
00:13:00,562 --> 00:13:04,127
[gasps]

178
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:07,491
{\an1}I don't have time to deal with
you three now. I'm sorry.

179
00:13:08,357 --> 00:13:09,223
{\an1}Please, just wait!

180
00:13:11,355 --> 00:13:14,353
{\an1}Shira! Why will you not fight
me right now?

181
00:13:15,353 --> 00:13:19,218
{\an1}You're quite strong. I knew that
the moment I blocked you.

182
00:13:19,684 --> 00:13:20,517
[grunt]

183
00:13:20,551 --> 00:13:22,483
{\an1}<i>That's why I won't fight you.</i>

184
00:13:23,184 --> 00:13:25,082
{\an1}Otherwise, one of us will get
hurt.

185
00:13:25,614 --> 00:13:27,613
{\an1}A shinobi fights despite the
risk!

186
00:13:29,312 --> 00:13:31,145
{\an1}<i>We have an important goal right</i>
<i>now... </i>

187
00:13:33,777 --> 00:13:37,642
{\an1}...to make sure as many Sand
entrants as possible make it
through the Exams.

188
00:13:38,774 --> 00:13:41,373
{\an1}You're helping other entrants?
But why?!

189
00:13:41,972 --> 00:13:47,302
{\an1}<i>Instead of asking questions, you</i>
<i>should worry about yourselves.</i>
<i>Sen, Yome,...Let's go! </i>

190
00:13:49,268 --> 00:13:50,435
Shira!

191
00:13:50,468 --> 00:13:51,801
{\an1}<i>The sand is moving!</i>

192
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:54,465
Huh?! [grunting]

193
00:13:54,999 --> 00:13:56,131
Lee! Help me!

194
00:13:56,364 --> 00:13:59,396
{\an1}I cannot! I am stuck! [grunting]

195
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:01,528
<i>Don't struggle!</i>
<i>You'll get pulled in deeper!</i>

196
00:14:01,561 --> 00:14:05,959
{\an1}[gasp] <i>It seems that I've</i>
<i>miscalculated our strategy...</i>

197
00:14:06,259 --> 00:14:07,425
{\an1}What do you mean?

198
00:14:08,792 --> 00:14:09,624
<i>Last night...</i>

199
00:14:11,123 --> 00:14:14,454
{\an1}<i>He was also busy analyzing the</i>
<i>Hidden Leaf's strengths.</i>

200
00:14:22,450 --> 00:14:24,783
{\an1}<i>They've had us under</i>
<i>surveillance from the start!</i>

201
00:14:25,915 --> 00:14:29,946
{\an1}<i>Not only that, but he took</i>
<i>command over the other Hidden</i>
<i>Sand entrants... </i>

202
00:14:30,945 --> 00:14:33,411
{\an1}<i>...and he ordered them not to</i>
<i>confront us. </i>

203
00:14:34,111 --> 00:14:40,440
{\an4}<i>That is why we did not encounter</i>
<i>any other teams! He is not only</i>
<i>skilled, he is very smart as</i>
